define({"topics":[{"title":"Creating a room for the first time","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">When accessing the Sametime server as an authenticated user for the first time, you         are guided into creating your own personal room. Personal rooms are secure and permanently         reserved for you. You can find your personal room on the <span class=\"keyword wintitle\">My Meetings<\/span>         tab of the Meetings homepage. The default personal room name is <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Sametime Meeting             Room<\/span>. To edit, refer to <a class=\"xref\" href=\"meetings_moderated_management.html\">meetings_moderated_management.html<\/a>.<\/p>","href":"t_personal_room.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_personal_room"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_personal_room-d459e243","topics":[]},{"title":"Starting an instant meeting","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\"> By default, anyone with the meeting link can access an instant meeting. All instant     meetings are added to the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Recent<\/span> tab in your Meetings homepage. Since     instant meetings are not owned or moderated, any authenticated user can start an existing     instant meeting. <\/p>","href":"generate_meetings.html","attributes":{"data-id":"generate_meetings.dita"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"generate_meetings.dita-d459e270","topics":[]},{"title":"Creating a new meeting","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Because meetings are configurable, user access and capability vary depending on how         the meeting is created. Some moderated meetings are configured to restrict guest access.         This topic covers the basic steps on how to create a new meeting. To learn how to manage         your meetings, refer to the <a class=\"xref\" href=\"participant_list.html\">participant_list.html<\/a> section. <\/p>","href":"t_create_moderated.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_create_moderated"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_create_moderated-d459e292","topics":[]}]});